<figureCitation box="[273,349,1738,1764]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1073,1097]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,179,1047]" captionTargetId="figure-19@2.[151,1436,179,1047]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Heteragrion calafatiensis sp. nov. male holotype from Pará, Brazil: habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405120" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405120/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="224">Figs. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[361,391,1738,1764]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1570,1594]" captionTargetBox="[177,1413,196,1533]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[151,1436,181,1546]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Heteragrion calafatiensis sp. nov., male holotypefrom Pará, Brazil:(a) head in dorsal view, (b) dorsal view of thorax, (c) terminal appendages in dorsal view, (d) terminal appendages in lateral view; Heteragrion chlorotaeniatum DeMarmels, 1989 male holotype from Río Negro, Venezuela: (e) terminal appendages in dorsal view, (f) terminal appendages in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405124" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405124/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="224">2a</figureCitation>
). Eyes yellow; labium and labrum brown; base of mandibles and genae pale, apex of mandibles black; antefrons pale yellow; vertex and remainder of head black, except for a curved pale yellow stripe connecting lateral ocelli with the antennae.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405120" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6405120" box="[151,1054,1073,1098]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405120/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="225" startId="2.[151,250,1073,1097]" targetBox="[151,1436,179,1047]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1054,1073,1098]" box="[151,1054,1073,1098]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,275,1073,1097]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">FIGURE 1.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Mendoza-Penagos &amp; Juen &amp; Vilela, 2022" authorityName="Mendoza-Penagos &amp; Juen &amp; Vilela" authorityYear="2022" box="[281,541,1073,1097]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="225" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="calafatiensis" status="sp. nov.">
