</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[547,628,1074,1098]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[547,628,1074,1098]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
male holotype from Pará, Brazil: habitus.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1180,1818]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">
<emphasis box="[199,280,1180,1206]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">Thorax</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[296,374,1180,1206]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1073,1097]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,179,1047]" captionTargetId="figure-19@2.[151,1436,179,1047]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Heteragrion calafatiensis sp. nov. male holotype from Pará, Brazil: habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405120" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405120/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">Figs. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[388,417,1180,1207]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1570,1594]" captionTargetBox="[177,1413,196,1533]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[151,1436,181,1546]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Heteragrion calafatiensis sp. nov., male holotypefrom Pará, Brazil:(a) head in dorsal view, (b) dorsal view of thorax, (c) terminal appendages in dorsal view, (d) terminal appendages in lateral view; Heteragrion chlorotaeniatum DeMarmels, 1989 male holotype from Río Negro, Venezuela: (e) terminal appendages in dorsal view, (f) terminal appendages in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405124" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405124/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">2b</figureCitation>
). Prothorax mostly yellow, lighter-colored laterally, with darker tones on dorsal areas: one brown stripe on each side of midline and another medial one; hind lobe rounded, mostly dark brown with yellow lateral stripes. Pterothorax with a black middorsal carina, and a thin pale yellow humeral stripe; mesepisternum mostly orange with a dark posterior spot; mesopleural suture pale yellow; mesepimeron dark orange; upper half of metepisternum pale yellow, remainder orange; remainder of pterothorax pale, except for a thin orange stripe on metepimeron. Coxae and trochanter pale yellow; femora alternating pale yellow and dark brown areas; tibiae brown; tarsi dark brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1180,1818]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">
<emphasis box="[199,267,1432,1457]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">Wings</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[282,346,1432,1458]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1073,1097]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,179,1047]" captionTargetId="figure-19@2.[151,1436,179,1047]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Heteragrion calafatiensis sp. nov. male holotype from Pará, Brazil: habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405120" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405120/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Hyaline, almost reaching S6 when closed; venation black, Pt dark brown; Pt overlying 3 cells in all wings, oblique proximally; 2 Pq cells in all wings; 18 Px in FW, 16 Px in HW.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1180,1818]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">
<emphasis box="[199,305,1504,1530]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">Abdomen</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[323,406,1504,1530]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1073,1097]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,179,1047]" captionTargetId="figure-19@2.[151,1436,179,1047]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Heteragrion calafatiensis sp. nov. male holotype from Pará, Brazil: habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405120" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405120/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">Fig. 1a</figureCitation>
). S1 pale yellow, with darker tones laterally and dorsally; S2 black dorsally, pale yellow laterally; S3–6 black with medially interrupted pale yellow basal rings and pale yellow medial stripes; S7 black with a thick medially interrupted pale yellow basal ring and a roughly quadrangular spot medially; S8–9 mostly black, pale yellow areas laterally; S10 orange laterally, with black borders and black dorsum.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1180,1818]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">
<emphasis box="[199,392,1648,1674]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">Anal appendages</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[405,526,1648,1675]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1570,1594]" captionTargetBox="[177,1413,196,1533]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[151,1436,181,1546]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Heteragrion calafatiensis sp. nov., male holotypefrom Pará, Brazil:(a) head in dorsal view, (b) dorsal view of thorax, (c) terminal appendages in dorsal view, (d) terminal appendages in lateral view; Heteragrion chlorotaeniatum DeMarmels, 1989 male holotype from Río Negro, Venezuela: (e) terminal appendages in dorsal view, (f) terminal appendages in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405124" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405124/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">Figs. 2c–d</figureCitation>
). Cercus dark brown with darker coloration especially on apex, carinas and spines; ventrobasal expansion absent; MP rounded, platelike morphology, rounded apex; ScP forming a small ridge bearing 4–5 denticles. Paraprocts pale yellow, posteriorly oriented, not reaching 1/2 of cercus, acute apex.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1180,1818]" box="[199,905,1756,1782]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">Measurements. FW 21.6; HW 20.9; Abdomen 32.3; Total 39.6.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1180,1818]" box="[199,418,1792,1818]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,1792,1818]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
